React is a JavaScript library used to build fast, interactive, and reusable user interfaces (UIs), especially for single-page applications (SPAs).
React helps developers build modern web applications by dividing the UI into small, reusable components.

Key Points
📌 Developed by Meta (formerly Facebook).
📌 Used to build dynamic and interactive websites.
📌 Component-based architecture.
📌 Uses a Virtual DOM for efficient updates.
📌 Makes UI development faster, easier, and more maintainable.

Example

Instead of writing the same HTML multiple times:
<button>Login</button>
<button>Login</button>
<button>Login</button>

In React, you create one reusable component:
function Button() {
  return <button>Login</button>;
}

Then use it multiple times:
<Button />
<Button />
<Button />

